And I saw them asking for $24 billion for a government stimulus.

00:32:35.687 --> 00:32:40.974
"Help us. Our car industry is in trouble."Now, when is this?

00:32:40.975 --> 00:32:46.853
I don't know. It could be years, it could be six months. I have no idea.

00:32:46.854 --> 00:32:51.049
I don't want to add to or take away from anything of when I saw this taking place.

00:32:51.050 --> 00:33:00.119
I said it's coming. This is what I saw coming in the days ahead. Could it be five years? Could it be two? I don't know.

00:33:00.120 --> 00:33:02.838
So, don't go, "Brandon, you said it was coming."Well, I don't know.

00:33:02.839 --> 00:33:15.879
I'm just telling you what I saw. So, I saw Chevrolet and GMC asking for help, too.

00:33:15.880 --> 00:33:27.881
"Hey, we want part of that. Help us out. Give us some money, too."So, I thought it was interesting.

00:33:27.882 --> 00:33:44.159
What else? Anything else? Okay, now this is interesting to me. Now, CNN—I do not like CNN—but this is them.

00:33:44.160 --> 00:34:03.430
While President Trump is actively trying to force them into a deal that is good for America, CNN is showcasing how Iranians are supposedly all pro-regime and preparing to take up arms.

00:34:03.431 --> 00:34:17.403
So, they're training little boys how to assemble an AK-47. You want to play it?

00:34:17.404 --> 00:34:36.309
Sorry. Yeah, that's that bomb, son. It sounds weird. Okay. How long is this?

00:34:36.310 --> 00:34:41.719
Okay. Here we go. I got it. It's still Trump and the battleship.

00:34:41.720 --> 00:34:57.599
I had to find escalating threats from the White House. Ordinary Iranians are now being urged to prepare for war.

00:34:57.600 --> 00:35:03.948
Right. Well, these rallies or gatherings have been taking place every single night for the past several weeks.

00:35:03.949 --> 00:35:09.399
And so, they're not new. But what is new is the introduction of weapons.

00:35:09.400 --> 00:35:25.929
And these kiosks have been set up in each of these squares where members of the military there—you can see them with masks on—they're showing people, in this case a woman, the basic skills of how to use what I think is an AK-47 or a Kalashnikov and things like that.

00:35:25.930 --> 00:35:31.474
Look over here. They're showing children how to use them as well.

00:35:31.475 --> 00:35:46.036
It's all part of a state-sponsored call to arms in case the war begins again. It's all guns on state television, too.

00:35:46.037 --> 00:35:52.279
Several Iranian channels are broadcasting their hosts brandishing assault rifles.

00:35:52.280 --> 00:36:02.559
'They gave me a weapon so I could learn how to use it like you,'this anchor tells her viewers.

00:36:02.560 --> 00:36:12.119
After his on-air training, this presenter fires off a round into the studio ceiling.

00:36:12.120 --> 00:36:28.259
But not all Iranians are gunning for a fight. Just around the corner from the rally, hints at the diversity. It's a very different atmosphere in this part of town.

00:36:28.260 --> 00:36:39.835
People are sitting with their partners, having coffees, strolling around the bookstores, or just hanging out with their friends.. People, you get very different views as well.

00:36:39.836 --> 00:36:53.559
People didn't want to talk on camera, but off camera, one said to me, '.'Another said she wanted to live in a normal world where there was a potential future for her children.

00:36:53.560 --> 00:37:02.799
But Iran's future to many Iranians looks increasingly clear, especially amid regular threats from President Trump.

00:37:02.800 --> 00:37:07.203
Waiting for the war. We're waiting. We are here because we know this war isn't over.

00:37:07.204 --> 00:37:16.866
We know he's not going to negotiate anything. He's just going to be like, they're not even trained soldiers. They're women up there.

00:37:16.867 --> 00:37:25.679
They're going to take up arms and they're going to just push them out front and be slaughtered if it happens that way. That's terrible. Now, listen to this.

00:37:25.680 --> 00:37:43.879
The Senate just passed a bill against Trump and wartime power today, and they're limiting him on how much power he has concerning this Iran war.

00:37:43.880 --> 00:37:56.079
What did the Lord show us about this? I saw Trump would be limited in the days ahead and that Israel would have to finish the job.

00:37:56.080 --> 00:38:06.559
And they used a missile that had a ball at the end of it that looked like it had eyes. And there were octagons.

00:38:06.560 --> 00:38:24.319
And all these octagons looked like they had eyes on this missile that was black and white that went out, and it was a ball at the end of it that was round when it shot off that looked like it was able to have octopus-like tentacles.

00:38:24.320 --> 00:38:47.946
Now, I don't know what that was, but I saw weapons, and the Lord said, 'Weapons that have never been used before are coming from Israel.'And I saw the mountain glowing where I'm seeing this uranium, plutonium, whatever it is, like in 'Back to the Future.'Uranium.

00:38:47.947 --> 00:38:51.240
And the Lord said, 'The mountain will glow.'And I saw it glowing.

00:38:51.241 --> 00:39:00.599
It was only in that mountain. But it was not America; it was Israel. America was not able to; Israel did it.

00:39:00.600 --> 00:39:08.399
Now, the US Senate advises measures to limit Trump's Iran war powers.

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:21.546
Louisiana Senator Bill Cassidy joins three other Republican lawmakers in supporting the measure. So we had Republicans turn on him today.

00:39:21.548 --> 00:39:47.559
Four of them, from what I understand, trying to say, 'We ain't doing this no more.'So the senators are turning their backs on Trump to try to block him from doing anything else, which is probably going to make him absolutely furious, I'm sure.

00:39:47.560 --> 00:40:00.165
It's symbolic and unlikely to become law. Advancing the resolution is a sign of growing frustration with the war.

00:40:00.166 --> 00:40:05.373
Now, will they do it? I don't know. So, do you think they're going to block it, Braden? What do you all think? Tell me.

00:40:05.374 --> 00:40:11.480
Do you think that they're going to end up making it where Trump can't make these decisions? Tell me in the comments down below.

00:40:11.481 --> 00:40:18.464
Do you think that they're going to end up blocking him and saying, 'We're not going to allow you to do this anymore.

00:40:18.465 --> 00:40:23.734
We're calling you back home. Cuba's next.'Well, what happens with all this?

00:40:23.735 --> 00:40:32.199
I'm curious where everybody's at with that. I saw Israel finishing the job.

00:40:32.200 --> 00:40:40.494
So, let's see what happens. Do you remember, Braden? Yes, I remember that.

00:40:40.495 --> 00:40:51.662
I say Israel finishes the job. America will not. We will save face trying to inject the economy with a great stimulus.

00:40:51.663 --> 00:41:08.244
And I saw a stimulus being passed around for households underneath $150,000, saying, 'Listen, if you make this amount, we're going to give you a certain amount of money for your household,'trying to get people to be excited.

00:41:08.245 --> 00:41:28.341
But let's see what happens. The US Senate advises a resolution to curb Trump's power to wage war on Iran.

00:41:28.342 --> 00:41:35.462
It's interesting to me. So I believe that's where we are. So we will continue to pray for President Trump.

00:41:35.463 --> 00:41:43.883
We will pray for President Trump and the peace that passes all understanding over Jerusalem, over all the things that we know to keep doing.

00:41:43.884 --> 00:41:48.181
Standing in the gap, praying for our nation, praying for revival.

00:41:48.182 --> 00:41:56.919
These are the main things I was thinking about today as I was taking care of the kids and doing things and helping out with Diana.

00:41:56.920 --> 00:42:04.626
I said, 'Lord, we always talk about revival and we always reflect on John G.

00:42:04.627 --> 00:42:10.333
Lake and Smith Wigglesworth and that was not our generation.

00:42:10.334 --> 00:42:18.712
Kathryn Kuhlman kind of was, and Oral Roberts, and Jack Coe, and William Branham and them.

00:42:18.713 --> 00:42:31.119
We see, we hear, and we have videos on YouTube that we reflect on and go, 'Wow,'but I'm so tired of talking about the past.

00:42:31.120 --> 00:42:39.679
As much as I honor those people and I go, 'Wow, it would have been really cool to be there.'What about today and what about now?

00:42:39.680 --> 00:43:01.199
I said, 'Lord, what about today?'I'm sitting here trying to find old things from Kathryn Kuhlman to feed on today before I did my broadcast, listening to old tent revivals from Oral Roberts and just feeding on the past and going, 'Man, when's our time?'And there has to be our time.

00:43:01.200 --> 00:43:07.635
I truly believe we're about to see the greatest harvest of souls this world has ever seen before.

00:43:07.636 --> 00:43:17.359
But it's not going to be something that we've seen before. He's going to do something that's never been seen before. Behold, he's going to do something new.

00:43:17.360 --> 00:43:24.828
But I told the Lord, I said, 'I don't want to focus on what people that are old, that have passed on, that are no longer here, did.

00:43:24.829 --> 00:43:37.199
I want to see something new in this generation. I want to see it with my sons, with my daughters, with the youth of this generation, with our young people.

00:43:37.200 --> 00:43:44.318
God, pour out your spirit one more time. Cause a major revival to flow over America.

00:43:44.319 --> 00:44:04.505
You said you were not done with America.'And this is not a revival where we go, 'Well, we rededicated America back to God.'I don't care about America being back to God; I want the church of America to be rededicated without this lukewarm church that I see.

00:44:04.506 --> 00:44:19.218
When you visit a church and you walk away not feeling stirred up, not feeling that you've got what it takes to conquer the week.

00:44:19.219 --> 00:44:40.754
When you walk away and you go, 'Well, that was a real good little whatever,'and you had some beautiful praise and worship because you've got paid musicians up there that are getting paid some of them almost six figures playing up there because they're trained musicians that are in it for the money and everything.

00:44:40.755 --> 00:45:07.399
I know a man's worthy of his hire, I'm not trying to always criticize, but I'm wanting to really emphasize: where is the true Holy Ghost church where we see the power of God flow through the auditorium and people delivered from demonic oppression and possession and the spirit of the Lord heals them from the top of their head to the soles of their feet?

00:45:07.400 --> 00:45:18.422
It's a fire shut up in my bones. And I hear some people when we talk to—because I love the South Koreans, they're some of the most beautiful-hearted praying people.

00:45:18.423 --> 00:45:23.279
I mean, my goodness, they're good folks. I love my South Korean channel.

00:45:23.280 --> 00:45:35.959
And it's amazing what the Lord has done over in South Korea with the people. They're so hungry. And I just look for the authentic.

00:45:35.960 --> 00:45:43.392
And then some of them say, 'Braden, we're experiencing that here.'We're experiencing it in Africa; there are parts of Africa where we're experiencing that.

00:45:43.393 --> 00:45:47.199
We get the emails. We're seeing revival. We're seeing this.

00:45:47.200 --> 00:45:50.997
Are you all not seeing anything like that? People are being raised from the dead.

00:45:50.998 --> 00:45:55.260
People are being healed. Blind eyes are opening. We're seeing those things.

00:45:55.261 --> 00:46:03.879
Are you not seeing that in America? I said, 'No, I don't think so.

00:46:03.880 --> 00:46:11.879
I don't see it in the circle we're in. But if it is happening, I want to be a part of it.

00:46:11.880 --> 00:46:21.415
I know I see some miracles that my friend, Billy Burke—he has healing services—but it's not like what I want to see: Acts chapter 2—raise the dead, walking on water.

00:46:21.416 --> 00:46:28.015
I mean, you know, I want to see some of that. I love it when people get healed of cancer and people's eyes get opened. It's amazing.

00:46:28.016 --> 00:46:45.386
Never lose your awe of God, but I'm wanting creative miracles: arms growing out, eyes popping back in, ears that weren't there, appendages that were not there coming back like the disciples.'And people are saying, 'Brandon, we're having that over here.'And I thought, 'What do we get to take in America?

00:46:45.387 --> 00:47:12.470
How do we have that?'I am on a mission. I was cleaning out my garage and blowing out the leaves from the winter and doing things, and the Lord stirred in my spirit: 'What does it take to see the dead raised when you need to see it raised?

00:47:12.471 --> 00:47:44.439
When you see somebody you love die or they're not here anymore and you know that there's Lazarus moments coming, that though you were dead yet shall you live.'When there's an anointing that needs to be pulled on and you see desperation in someone's eyes, is it there to bring forth the miracle that they're believing for, to pull on that anointing?

00:47:44.440 --> 00:48:04.159
What does it take? And I go over things that I hear my elder generals talk about, like Billy and Billy, both Billies, and they talk about the sufferings and sharing His suffering and the greater glory and things that are attached to it. And I just go, 'Lord, show me.

00:48:04.160 --> 00:48:35.879
What is the switch to flip on the light in the darkness, that Your light is shining on our face like Moses, that when they see us, we're wall-to-wall Holy Ghost?'But it's not just something that we confess and we're parroting something, but it's actual manifestation that when we walk in the room, the shadow touches and they're healed and they rise up and walk.

00:48:35.880 --> 00:48:54.218
When the anointing that was on the disciples is tangible on us and it's not something that we just experience once, but we walk in it on a day-to-day basis. What is it that takes that? Is it the persecution?

00:48:54.219 --> 00:49:08.639
Because when I was praying for Africa and we were on here praying and we saw the people of Nigeria, I believe it was, and I saw their flag, and the Lord said, 'The greater the persecution, the greater the anointing.

00:49:08.640 --> 00:49:18.559
The greater the persecution, the greater the presence and the power and the glory comes with the anointing.

00:49:18.560 --> 00:49:30.783
For these sufferings bring forth the greater glory.'When Paul and Silas...

00:49:30.784 --> 00:49:45.079
Peter was in the prison, and then you have these moments where the church prayed and they interceded and they were able to get the gates opened.

00:49:45.080 --> 00:49:50.643
They were able, with guards on both sides watching over them in the middle of the prison.

00:49:50.644 --> 00:50:02.281
And they didn't want, because they knew that they had some kind of supernatural ability and they had been assigned these guards on both sides.

00:50:02.282 --> 00:50:10.799
And Peter's asleep knowing that tomorrow he's going to die.

00:50:10.800 --> 00:50:17.679
I don't know about you, but if I get some kind of bad report, it's hard to sleep sometimes. You go, 'Oh, man,'because your mind's running.

00:50:17.680 --> 00:50:28.559
But you have so much confidence and you're so fully persuaded that you're in the prison and you're snoring and an angel has to wake you up: 'Get up!

00:50:28.560 --> 00:50:49.559
Get up!'But the prayers of the saints—why we have this channel—the prayers of the early church had enough to get the guards knocked out, open the prison door, open the gate, and get him free.

00:50:49.560 --> 00:50:56.759
What kind of prayer, what kind of intercession does it take to open a gate?

00:50:56.760 --> 00:51:05.079
A supernatural opening of the gate? What kind of prayer does it take to open the prison door?

00:51:05.080 --> 00:51:16.159
When someone's wrongly being accused in these last days, what kind of prayer does it take for a church to bring forth just a little revival and some fire in your church?

00:51:16.160 --> 00:51:28.759
That it's not church usual, it's church unusual. And that's what I'm just like, because the Lord said, 'What are you looking for?'I said, 'I'm looking for more.

00:51:28.760 --> 00:51:37.119
I'm not satisfied with the status quo. I am so done with church usual.

00:51:37.120 --> 00:51:45.216
I want church unusual. I want to see fire shut up in my bones. I want to see what Oral Roberts saw.

00:51:45.217 --> 00:51:53.799
And I want to see and experience more than what Kathryn Kuhlman experienced.

00:51:53.800 --> 00:52:01.883
If not, I said, if not, then why not? Why not me? Why then? What? You know, Lord, I know they went through things.

00:52:01.884 --> 00:52:11.719
I know I've been through some things, but Lord, what turns on that switch?

00:52:11.720 --> 00:52:30.311
Because the only thing that's ever going to change America is whenever the sons and the daughters, us, become who we're called to be and rise up and stop trying to just always pray for revival, but let revival start with us and say, 'Here am I, Lord.

00:52:30.312 --> 00:52:40.098
Send me.'But don't send me with no power. I want them to marvel at the ignorance of Brandon Biggs.

00:52:40.099 --> 00:52:47.626
Whenever he speaks, they go, 'He has been with Jesus.'There's something different about him. Why?

00:52:47.627 --> 00:52:54.303
It's not about giving glory to Brandon, but there's something different about what's on that man.

00:52:54.304 --> 00:53:05.264
And it's Jesus. Because he had been with Jesus. They marveled because they knew they were unlearned and ignorant men.

00:53:05.265 --> 00:53:11.416
But they knew they had been with Jesus. How'd they know that?

00:53:11.417 --> 00:53:18.359
Because the glory was there. The manifested presence was there.

00:53:18.360 --> 00:53:25.599
Because when God shows up on the scene, He changes the atmosphere.

00:53:25.600 --> 00:53:39.062
And when you go into a church and the atmosphere is dull, like touching a cold stove, and it's week after week...

00:53:39.063 --> 00:53:50.800
I'm not trying to pick at the church I used to work for, but week after week you go into a church and you go, 'I work here.

00:53:50.801 --> 00:54:04.894
I get a check here, but it is dead as touching a cold stove.'And yet people are getting blessed by it because you've got somebody playing some good music or whatever sermons.

00:54:04.895 --> 00:54:16.399
Okay. But I go, 'Why are we playing church?'God came to save and set the captives free.

00:54:16.400 --> 00:54:51.399
'I come to save that which was lost.'And now in Acts 4, this is my favorite: 'Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned and ignorant men, they marveled and took knowledge of them that they had been with Jesus.'It's not just being with Him one time.

00:54:51.400 --> 00:55:01.916
It's being with Him day after day, sitting at His feet and having a relationship with Him.

00:55:01.917 --> 00:55:10.159
I told you more people would go home. James Robison went home yesterday. We have more generals going home.

00:55:10.160 --> 00:55:14.856
And the Lord said there will be a changing of the guard, a passing of the baton in the days ahead.

00:55:14.857 --> 00:55:25.319
And you're going to see the major generals that have been in the past start to transition home.

00:55:25.320 --> 00:55:28.209
He said, 'I'm raising up new voices. I'm raising up a new generation.

00:55:28.210 --> 00:55:40.879
I'm raising up new generals to those that I've called that say, "Yes, here am I, Lord, send me."You're the closers.'They had their time and this generation is going to start to go home.

00:55:40.880 --> 00:55:55.799
And the Lord said, 'You're going to see more and more of it through the summer.'We just had another one, a third one: Marilyn Hickey, Joni, and now Pat—and I only say, 'Well, who's next?'I don't know.

00:55:55.800 --> 00:56:03.089
But there are going to be more transitions. I saw certain major ministries going home.

00:56:03.090 --> 00:56:11.119
Some of them huge, huge ministries. And it will get world attention.

00:56:11.120 --> 00:56:17.808
Huge. And Pat Robertson was a huge ministry. Joni, I mean, they're all pretty...

00:56:17.809 --> 00:56:21.639
they were all pretty big ministries."Marilyn Hickey, all of them.

00:56:21.640 --> 00:56:34.030
So, we see a transition. When people step out and go home, there's a void.

00:56:34.031 --> 00:56:42.559
One needs to rise up. Will you be that person? They're up there rooting for us right now.

00:56:42.560 --> 00:56:50.683
Their cloud of witnesses say, 'Will you help finish the race? Don't let the baton drop.

00:56:50.684 --> 00:57:00.678
Keep running with this end-time army.'And I know there's more going home soon.

00:57:00.679 --> 00:57:08.959
The Lord said it; He told me. He said specific ones to me, and I've never—don't make that public.

00:57:08.960 --> 00:57:20.439
So I just want to stir you up today to not give up on your dreams of what God's called you to do just because you didn't see it manifest in the first years of when you thought it should.

00:57:20.440 --> 00:57:28.799
God knows when you're able to handle it, and when the time is, and when it's time for you to rise up and be who you need to be.

00:57:28.800 --> 00:57:35.719
Humble yourself. Even if it's to say, 'Hey, I'm going to go volunteer at a church and be a janitor.

00:57:35.720 --> 00:57:42.131
Do whatever it takes to get the gospel out.'Diana, we were talking about it when we worked at the church.

00:57:42.133 --> 00:57:54.239
The guest speaker usually gets the most praise. They get in late, they leave early.

00:57:54.240 --> 00:58:03.875
The janitor, like me—I was cleaning the bathrooms until sometimes 1:00 or 2:00 in the morning after the service. You go in there and it's dark.

00:58:03.876 --> 00:58:17.839
It's like crickets, and you set up the chairs, you vacuum the aisles, you're making sure all the diapers are cleaned out of the nurseries, and you do that time and time again—the least thanked position.

00:58:17.840 --> 00:58:38.559
But without that janitor, without that offering counter, without the usher, without the greeter, without the parking lot attendant, without the nursery worker, that guest speaker or whoever it was for the revival couldn't have gotten the job done the way they did.

00:58:38.560 --> 00:59:13.066
Because if the bathrooms were stinky, the floors had urine on them, somebody just took a dump all over the stool, you've got all this nasty stuff going on, and you're going, 'This is the stinkiest bathroom I ever walked in,'and you go, 'I don't even want to go into that church and listen to this guy.'Don't ever underestimate the importance of who you are and how you bring forth the atmosphere for that person to receive what Jesus is about to speak through that speaker.

00:59:13.067 --> 00:59:45.359
Your part was just as important as the speaker's was. And I remember setting up the chairs, cleaning up the vomit when somebody wrote poo on the wall, wipe their booty on my wall and write it out in numbers—'poo'or whatever they want to say, just being disgusting with their feces, doing some of the most filthy, vile things I've ever seen in a bathroom. I cleaned it for 15 years of my life.

00:59:45.360 --> 01:00:24.399
And I remember every single time going home and thinking, 'Man, I just wanted to make it where if they came in and it smelled good, if they walked into the bathroom and it didn't smell like stuff or nurseries or whatever and their kids didn't go home sick and they said, "Our kids always come to church and play on the church equipment and they're always leaving with a cold or a virus because they spread it around."'I kept even the church nursery toys clean with bleach and whatever, making sure they didn't spread viruses around during flu season.

01:00:24.400 --> 01:00:37.039
Always trying to think outside the box. If my kid was in here, how do you make sure that the virus from these flu bugs kids are passing around stays out?

01:00:37.040 --> 01:00:46.439
Always going the extra mile, making it so if you don't show up, they're going to notice.

01:00:46.440 --> 01:00:52.759
And there's many of you that may do that right now at your church. And I'm telling you, it's all hands on deck.

01:00:52.760 --> 01:00:59.639
Never ever take your position of what God's called you to do lightly.

01:00:59.640 --> 01:01:06.239
For if it wasn't for people like you, the job wouldn't be done as effective as it should have been.

01:01:06.240 --> 01:01:21.919
And I'm trying to tell you right now, the same reward that the person's going to get up there preaching with the fire—you think, 'Oh boy, they've got it all made'—man, great is the reward of those that do what we've done.

01:01:21.920 --> 01:01:35.119
The person who counts the offerings, the person who makes sure the bills are paid so that the lights are on when they showed up, making sure the water bill was paid so the toilet would flush.

01:01:35.120 --> 01:01:42.879
Never take for granted what God has called you to do and do it with all your heart.

01:01:42.880 --> 01:01:48.050
That's what we did and we continue to do. I still feel like I'm the janitor.

01:01:48.051 --> 01:02:02.039
I still feel like my wife is the offering counter and the data entry person, always behind the scenes trying just to make it.

01:02:02.040 --> 01:02:08.519
Be thankful for where you are and know that your reward is great when you get on the other side.

01:02:08.520 --> 01:02:15.359
Keep your head up. And that's my message for what I felt in my heart tonight.

01:02:15.360 --> 01:02:24.079
I said, 'Lord, what is it going to take? I'm so hungry for authentic.

01:02:24.080 --> 01:02:49.359
